observations.recommendation:
We reiterated recommended that the Municipal Mayor enact measures to:

(i) To exert every effort to correct the noted delays caused by an employee’s dual function and;

(ii) Avoid granting additional Cash Advances for travelling expenses to employees with pending unliquidated cash advances and resort to reimbursement scheme for unavoidable travel claims.

7.7. We recommended and management agreed to enact measures to:
a. Enforce the immediate liquidation of Cash Advances by
concerned officials and employees by sending demand letters;
noting that sanctions may be enforced should they fail to settle
their advances by withholding their salary;
b. Ensure that Cash Advances be liquidated in accordance with the
provisions of COA Circular No. 79-002 dated February 10, 1997;
and
c. To exert every effort to correct the noted delays caused by an
employee’s dual function.

8.5. We recommended and management agreed to enact measures to:
a. Enforce the immediate liquidation of Cash Advances by
concerned officials and employees by sending demand letters;
noting that sanctions may be enforced should they fail to settle
their advances by withholding their salary;
b. Ensure that Cash Advances be liquidated in accordance with the
provisions of COA Circular No. 79-002 dated February 10, 1997;
and
c. To exert every effort to correct the noted delays caused by an
employee’s dual function.

We recommended that Management:
Require the members of the BAC to equip and update themselves of the existing GPPB guidelines which are exempted from the provisions of RA No. 9184 in response to COVID-19 outbreak;
Require the accounting office to submit immediately the Omnibus Sworn Statement and any of those mentioned in Item 5 of GPPB Circular No. 01-2020, whichever is applicable;
Require the Budget Office to submit the necessary approved APP;
Require the BAC to furnish COA of the Notices of Award and ensure the posting of the approved APP and NOAs and POs for these transactions

We recommended and the following LGU officials and personnel agreed that:

3.7.1	The Mayor, if possible, refrain from designating key personnel of the LGU like the accountant, treasurer, budget officer, and the like, to head the Inventory Committee.  Chairmanship of the Committee already entails big and complex duties which already a burden if added to their existing great responsibilities;

3.7.2	The designated Inventory Committee Chairperson to initiate the planning and conduct periodic physical inventory of the supplies and property of the LGU as mandated in Section 124 of the NGAS Manual.  The RPCPPE and RPCI prepared by the Committee as a result of the inventory taking, shall be reconciled with the accounting records.  These Reports shall also be submitted to COA pursuant to Section 124 of NGAS Manual for LGU;

3.7.3	The Property Custodian to make and maintain a list of all the supplies and property of the LGU, with complete information thereof reflected therein like the name and description of the supply or property, serial number, property number, cost, etc.  The list shall be reconciled with the similar records in the accounting at least a quarter;

3.7.4	The Municipal Accountant to maintain Supplies, PPEs and other properties Ledger Cards, as well as complete list/schedule of the same.  Reconcile the accounting records with the list/reports being kept by the Property Custodian at least quarterly;

3.7.5	The Property Custodian to property tag every PPE including the breeding stocks.  This will help in easy and fast monitoring of the assets and identification thereof in case a loss of the same;

3.7.6	The Property Custodian to provide PAR to every PPE issued to respective end users.  Accountability to the property redounds to the latter; and

3.7.7	Adhere to Sections 119, 120 and 124 of the NGAS Manual, Volume 1, Section 3(c), Chapter   V   of   the   Manual   on   Property Custodianship, and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations governing the conduct of physical count of properties, maintenance of records and submission of reports thereof to the Auditor.

